<TITLE> Market continues to rally in opening trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 06 (bdnews24.com)  Indices on the Dhaka Stock Exchange continued to rally in opening trade Thursday amid investor buying. Banks dominated the turnover board followed with issues in pharmaceuticals and chemicals, mutual funds, insurance. An IPO by Delta BRAC Housing Finance Corporation has also kept investors' busy for the last four days. DBH is floating 5 lakh shares at a face value of Tk 100 each and a premium value of Tk 110. The subscription which, opened on Mar 2 closes Thursday. An official of a brokerage house told bdnews24.com that DBH being the first IPO of the year created some hype in the market. Overall, the market witnessed a sharp rise in the general index at the start of trade and remained upbeat thereafter. At 12.29 pm, the benchmark DGEN or general index was up 48.39 points or 1.63 percent at 3005.87, while the DSI or all share price index was at 2539.15, up 37.58 points or 1.50 percent. Turnover stood at Tk 1.92 billion from 11,820,188 traded shares. Gainers beat losers 194 to 30 while three issues held steady. Most banks advanced with a few falling on profit taking. At 12.29 pm, AB Bank was selling up at Tk 3440 from Tk 3335.75. The bank has decided to raise its authorised capital to Tk 4 billion from the existing Tk 2 billion, awaiting approval from the central bank and market regulator, according to the DSE website. Square Pharma also continued to gain, selling up at Tk 3560 from Wednesday's Tk 3536.50. Grameen Mutual Fund One rose to Tk 123.50 from the previous day's closing of Tk 122. Beximco Pharma advanced to Tk 68 from Tk 64.70. Apex Adelchi Footwear climbed to Tk 2462.50 from Wednesday's Tk 2238.75. Among the other issues on the turnover board, Keya Cosmetics, IFIC, Fareast Life Insurance and NCC Bank rose. Uttara Bank fell on profit taking. bdn
